start-details:

h2: Geo Join Node

This node performs a spatial join between two datasets based on their geographic coordinates. It matches records from the two datasets that are within a specified distance or intersect with each other.

end-details:

start-examples:

h2: Geo Join Node Example

Given two datasets:

Dataset 1 (Suppliers):

SupplierID	SupplierName	Region	YearsInBusiness	LeadTime	PriceIndex	OrderFulfillmentTime	OverallCost	OrderCancellations	CustomerRating	Latitude	Longitude	Polygon
S1	Supplier A	Region 1	10	5	1.2	3	100	2	4	40.7128	-74.0060	...
S2	Supplier B	Region 2	15	7	1.1	4	120	1	5	34.0522	-118.2437	...


Dataset 2 (Parts):

PartID	SupplierID	PartName	PartCategory	PartQualityScore
P1	S1	Bolt	Hardware	8
P2	S2	Nut	Hardware	7
P3	S3	Screw	Hardware	9

If you configure the Geo Join node to join the datasets based on the Latitude and Longitude columns, and you specify a distance threshold of 50 kilometers, the output would be:

SupplierID	SupplierName	Region	YearsInBusiness	LeadTime	PriceIndex	OrderFulfillmentTime	OverallCost	OrderCancellations	CustomerRating	Latitude	Longitude	Polygon	PartID	PartName	PartCategory	PartQualityScore
S1	Supplier A	Region 1	10	5	1.2	3	100	2	4	40.7128	-74.0060	...	P1	Bolt	Hardware	8

end-examples:
